{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871169538,"sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2b823c001W2ZbbM0ExX7ZCB","messageID":"msg_d7a2b7571001vfOFNt4osdhxpl","sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Valkey Storage Implementation\n2: \n3: ## AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `pkg/store` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | S (Small) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement a Valkey storage provider as an alternative to the existing Redis backend for the Session Store interface. This proposal delivers a production-ready Valkey implementation that:\n17: \n18: 1. **Implements the Store Interface**: Full implementation of all 8 Store methods using `valkey-go` client\n19: 2. **Provides Atomic Operations**: `DoMulti`-based multi-command transactions for data consistency\n20: 3. **Maintains Secondary Indexes**: ZSET-based expiry and activity tracking for efficient garbage collection\n21: 4. **Supports Configuration via Environment**: Flexible connection, authentication, and client behavior setup\n22: \n23: This implementation enables AgentCube to use Valkey as an alternative session metadata backend, providing deployment flexibility and vendor neutrality while maintaining full compatibility with the existing Redis-based data model.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Scope\n28: \n29: ### In Scope\n30: \n31: | Item | Detail |\n32: |------|--------|\n33: | **Valkey Implementation** | `store_valkey.go` — Complete Store interface implementation |\n34: | **Connection Management** | Environment-based Valkey client configuration |\n35: | **Atomic Operations** | `DoMulti` for SETNX + ZADD, DEL + ZREM |\n36: | **Error Handling** | Valkey-specific error translation to `ErrNotFound` |\n37: | **Index Management** | ZSET operations for expiry and last-activity tracking |\n38: | **Helper Functions** | Key generation, JSON serialization, batch loading via MGET |\n39: | **Singleton Update** | Extend `singleton.go` to support `STORE_TYPE=valkey` |\n40: \n41: ### Out of Scope\n42: \n43: - Changes to `Store` interface definition\n44: - Modifications to `SandboxInfo` type or serialization format\n45: - New features beyond existing Redis functionality\n46: - Migration tooling between Redis and Valkey backends\n47: - Changes to client-go or other packages\n48: - Redis Cluster-specific hash tag handling (deployment consideration)\n49: - TLS/SSL configuration (handled via library defaults)\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## Design\n54: \n55: ### File Structure\n56: \n57: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n58: |------|------|--------------|\n59: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation with valkey-go | ~200 |\n60: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Update singleton to support valkey type | ~+10 |\n61: \n62: ### Valkey Implementation (`valkeyStore`)\n63: \n64: ```go\n65: type valkeyStore struct {\n66:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n67:     sessionPrefix        string          // \"session:\"\n68:     expiryIndexKey       string          // \"session:expiry\"\n69:     lastActivityIndexKey string          // \"session:last_activity\"\n70: }\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ### Key Patterns\n74: \n75: | Pattern | Value | Description |\n76: |---------|-------|-------------|\n77: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session data keys |\n78: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET for expiry tracking |\n79: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET for activity tracking |\n80: | Session Key | `session:{sessionID}` | Primary key format |\n81: \n82: ### Environment Configuration\n83: \n84: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n85: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n86: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection; set to `valkey` (case-insensitive) |\n87: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Valkey server addresses (comma-separated for cluster) |\n88: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive) |\n89: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | - | Set to `true` to enable `DisableCache` option |\n90: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | - | Set to `true` to enable `ForceSingleClient` option |\n91: \n92: ### Connection Options\n93: \n94: ```go\n95: valkey.ClientOption{\n96:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n97:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n98:     DisableCache: disableCache,       // from VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\n99:     ForceSingleClient: forceSingle,   // from VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## Operations Specification\n106: \n107: ### Ping — Connectivity Verification\n108: \n109: ```\n110: Ping(ctx)\n111:     │\n112:     ▼\n113: B().Ping() command\n114:     │\n115:     ▼\n116: Expect \"PONG\" string response\n117:     │\n118:     ▼\n119: Return nil if PONG, error otherwise\n120: ```\n121: \n122: **Valkey API**: `B().Ping()`\n123: **Response**: String \"PONG\"\n124: \n125: ### GetSandboxBySessionID — Retrieve by ID\n126: \n127: ```\n128: GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n129:     │\n130:     ▼\n131: B().Get().Key(session:{sessionID})\n132:     │\n133:     ▼\n134: If IsValkeyNil:\n135:     └── Return ErrNotFound\n136: If other error:\n137:     └── Return wrapped error\n138: If success:\n139:     └── Unmarshal JSON → *SandboxInfo\n140: ```\n141: \n142: **Valkey API**: `B().Get().Key(key)`\n143: **Error Translation**: `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound`\n144: \n145: ### StoreSandbox — Atomic Create with Indexing\n146: \n147: ```\n148: StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n149:     │\n150:     ▼\n151: Validate: sandbox != nil\n152:     │\n153:     ▼\n154: Validate: !sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero()\n155:     │\n156:     ▼\n157: Serialize to JSON\n158:     │\n159:     ▼\n160: DoMulti:\n161: ├─ SETNX session:{id} <json>\n162: ├─ ZADD session:expiry <expiresAt.Unix()> {id}\n163: └─ ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix()> {id}\n164:     │\n165:     ▼\n166: Execute DoMulti\n167:     │\n168:     ▼\n169: If any error: return error\n170: ```\n171: \n172: **Valkey API**: `SETNX`, `ZADD` via `DoMulti`\n173: **Atomicity**: All commands executed in single `DoMulti` block\n174: \n175: ### UpdateSandbox — Update Existing Record\n176: \n177: ```\n178: UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n179:     │\n180:     ▼\n181: Validate: sandbox != nil\n182:     │\n183:     ▼\n184: Serialize to JSON\n185:     │\n186:     ▼\n187: B().Set().Key(key).Value(json).XX()\n188:     │\n189:     ▼\n190: If response ToString() != \"OK\":\n191:     └── Return error: \"key not exists\"\n192: If success:\n193:     └── Return nil\n194:     \n195: Note: Does NOT modify ZSET indices\n196: ```\n197: \n198: **Valkey API**: `SET ... XX`\n199: **Behavior**: XX flag requires key to exist; check OK response\n200: \n201: ### DeleteSandboxBySessionID — Atomic Cleanup\n202: \n203: ```\n204: DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n205:     │\n206:     ▼\n207: DoMulti:\n208: ├─ DEL session:{id}\n209: ├─ ZREM session:expiry {id}\n210: └─ ZREM session:last_activity {id}\n211:     │\n212:     ▼\n213: Execute DoMulti\n214:     │\n215:     ▼\n216: Return error if any command fails\n217: ```\n218: \n219: **Valkey API**: `DEL`, `ZREM` via `DoMulti`\n220: **Atomicity**: All cleanup operations in single `DoMulti` block\n221: \n222: ### ListExpiredSandboxes — Query by Expiry\n223: \n224: ```\n225: ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n226:     │\n227:     ▼\n228: If limit <= 0:\n229:     └── Return nil, nil\n230:     │\n231:     ▼\n232: Zrangebyscore session:expiry Min(\"-inf\") Max(\"{before.Unix()}\") Limit(0, limit)\n233:     │\n234:     ▼\n235: MGET session:{id1} session:{id2} ...\n236:     │\n237:     ▼\n238: For each result:\n239:     ├─ If not empty: unmarshal and add to results\n240:     └─ If empty (orphan): skip\n241:     │\n242:     ▼\n243: Return []*SandboxInfo\n244: ```\n245: \n246: **Valkey API**: `Zrangebyscore` + `Mget`\n247: **Tolerance**: Missing keys (orphan ZSET members) are skipped\n248: **Note**: MGET requires keys in same slot for clustered deployments\n249: \n250: ### ListInactiveSandboxes — Query by Activity\n251: \n252: ```\n253: ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n254:     │\n255:     ▼\n256: If limit <= 0:\n257:     └── Return nil, nil\n258:     │\n259:     ▼\n260: Zrangebyscore session:last_activity Min(\"-inf\") Max(\"{before.Unix()}\") Limit(0, limit)\n261:     │\n262:     ▼\n263: MGET session:{id1} session:{id2} ...\n264:     │\n265:     ▼\n266: For each result:\n267:     ├─ If not empty: unmarshal and add to results\n268:     └─ If empty (orphan): skip\n269:     │\n270:     ▼\n271: Return []*SandboxInfo\n272: ```\n273: \n274: **Valkey API**: `Zrangebyscore` (on activity index) + `Mget`\n275: **Note**: Same pattern as ListExpiredSandboxes, different ZSET key\n276: \n277: ### UpdateSessionLastActivity — Bump Activity Timestamp\n278: \n279: ```\n280: UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)\n281:     │\n282:     ▼\n283: Validate: sessionID != \"\"\n284:     │\n285:     ▼\n286: If at.IsZero():\n287:     └── at = time.Now()\n288:     │\n289:     ▼\n290: B().Exists().Key(session:{sessionID})\n291:     │\n292:     ▼\n293: If result != 1:\n294:     └── Return ErrNotFound\n295:     │\n296:     ▼\n297: B().Zadd().Key(session:last_activity).ScoreMember(float64(at.Unix()), sessionID)\n298:     │\n299:     ▼\n300: Return error if ZADD fails\n301: ```\n302: \n303: **Valkey API**: `Exists`, `Zadd`\n304: **Semantics**: Returns ErrNotFound if session doesn't exist\n305: \n306: ### Close — Graceful Shutdown\n307: \n308: ```\n309: Close()\n310:     │\n311:     ▼\n312: vs.cli.Close()\n313:     │\n314:     ▼\n315: Return nil\n316: ```\n317: \n318: **Valkey API**: `Close()` on valkey client\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ## Helper Functions\n323: \n324: ### Key Generation\n325: \n326: ```go\n327: func (vs *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n328:     return vs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n329: }\n330: ```\n331: \n332: ### Batch Loading\n333: \n334: ```go\n335: func (vs *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, ids []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n336: ```\n337: \n338: - Builds keys from session IDs using `sessionKey`\n339: - Uses single `Mget` for efficiency\n340: - Skips empty string results (orphan handling)\n341: - Unmarshals JSON for valid results\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ## Error Handling\n346: \n347: | Scenario | Valkey Response | Return Value |\n348: |----------|-----------------|--------------|\n349: | Key not found | `IsValkeyNil` | `ErrNotFound` |\n350: | Connection error | Connection error | Wrapped error |\n351: | DoMulti error | Command error | Command error |\n352: | SETXX miss | Response not OK | `errors.New(\"key not exists\")` |\n353: | Nil sandbox | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")` |\n354: | Zero ExpiresAt | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"ExpiresAt is zero\")` |\n355: | Empty sessionID | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"session id is empty\")` |\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ## Impact Analysis\n360: \n361: ### Files Created/Modified\n362: \n363: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n364: |------|-------------|-------------|\n365: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | ~200 | Valkey implementation |\n366: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | ~+10 | Add valkeyStoreType selector |\n367: \n368: ### Dependencies Added\n369: \n370: ```go\n371: import (\n372:     \"context\"\n373:     \"encoding/json\"\n374:     \"errors\"\n375:     \"fmt\"\n376:     \"os\"\n377:     \"strings\"\n378:     \"sync\"\n379:     \"time\"\n380:     \n381:     \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n382:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n383:     \n384:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n385: )\n386: ```\n387: \n388: | Package | Purpose |\n389: |---------|---------|\n390: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n391: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging for initialization errors |\n392: \n393: ### Provider Selection (singleton.go)\n394: \n395: Extend `initStore()` to support `valkeyStoreType`:\n396: \n397: ```go\n398: const (\n399:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n400:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n401: )\n402: \n403: func initStore() error {\n404:     storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n405:     if storeType == \"\" {\n406:         storeType = redisStoreType\n407:     }\n408:     \n409:     switch storeType {\n410:     case redisStoreType:\n411:         // existing Redis init\n412:     case valkeyStoreType:\n413:         // new Valkey init\n414:     default:\n415:         return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %s\", storeType)\n416:     }\n417: }\n418: ```\n419: \n420: ### Downstream Consumers\n421: \n422: | Consumer | Usage |\n423: |----------|-------|\n424: | Session Manager | `Storage()` accessor for session CRUD |\n425: | Idle Cleanup Worker | `ListInactiveSandboxes` for GC |\n426: | Expiry Cleanup Worker | `ListExpiredSandboxes` for GC |\n427: \n428: ### Performance Characteristics\n429: \n430: | Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n431: |-----------|------------|-------|\n432: | Get | O(1) | Single key lookup |\n433: | Store | O(1) per command | `DoMulti` of 3 commands |\n434: | Update | O(1) | Single SET with XX |\n435: | Delete | O(1) per command | `DoMulti` of 3 commands |\n436: | List (expired/inactive) | O(log n + m) | Zrangebyscore + MGET |\n437: | Activity Update | O(log n) | Zadd on sorted set |\n438: \n439: ---\n440: \n441: ## Alternatives Considered\n442: \n443: ### Alternative 1: Use Redis Client for Valkey (Protocol Compatibility)\n444: \n445: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n446: |--------|------------|\n447: | **Pros** | No additional dependency; Valkey is Redis protocol-compatible |\n448: | **Cons** | Misses Valkey-specific optimizations; unclear semantics |\n449: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Native Valkey client provides better performance, clearer dependencies, and access to Valkey-specific features |\n450: \n451: ### Alternative 2: Unified Client Abstraction\n452: \n453: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n454: |--------|------------|\n455: | **Pros** | Single interface for all backends; reduced code duplication |\n456: | **Cons** | Adds complexity; clients have different API shapes; harder to maintain |\n457: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Separate implementations are clearer; `sync.Once` singleton already provides clean provider selection |\n458: \n459: ### Alternative 3: Plugin Architecture\n460: \n461: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n462: |--------|------------|\n463: | **Pros** | Dynamic backend loading; extensible without recompilation |\n464: | **Cons** | Over-engineering for 2 backends; Go plugins are complex and less idiomatic |\n465: | **Decision** | **Rejected** (Future consideration) — Can be revisited if 3+ backends become necessary |\n466: \n467: ### Alternative 4: Continue with Redis Only\n468: \n469: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n470: |--------|------------|\n471: | **Pros** | Single backend to maintain; proven implementation |\n472: | **Cons** | No vendor choice; Valkey adoption growing; licensing preferences vary |\n473: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Low implementation cost; provides valuable deployment flexibility |\n474: \n475: ---\n476: \n477: ## Risks and Mitigations\n478: \n479: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n480: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n481: | Valkey client library differences | Low | Medium | Thorough testing; handle `IsValkeyNil` vs Redis `Nil` |\n482: | MGET slot alignment (clustered Valkey) | Low | Low | Document deployment consideration; use hashtag patterns if needed |\n483: | Dependency maintenance | Low | Low | Valkey Go client actively maintained by Valkey IO project |\n484: | Configuration complexity | Low | Low | Clear documentation; validation at startup |\n485: | Connection failure at startup | Low | High | `initStore` logs fatal via klog; operator must check configuration |\n486: | Orphan ZSET members after partial failures | Low | Low | List loaders skip missing keys; periodic full scan can clean up |\n487: \n488: ---\n489: \n490: ## Verification\n491: \n492: ### Unit Tests\n493: \n494: ```bash\n495: # Run all store tests\n496: make test PKG=./pkg/store/...\n497: \n498: # Run with race detector\n499: go test -race ./pkg/store/...\n500: \n501: # Run specific Valkey tests\n502: go test -v ./pkg/store/... -run \"TestValkey\"\n503: ```\n504: \n505: ### Integration Tests (requires Valkey)\n506: \n507: ```bash\n508: # Start Valkey\n509: docker run -d -p 6379:6379 valkey/valkey:latest\n510: \n511: # Run integration tests\n512: go test -v ./pkg/store/... -tags=integration -valkey-addr=localhost:6379\n513: ```\n514: \n515: ### Manual Verification\n516: \n517: ```bash\n518: # Build verification\n519: go build ./pkg/store/...\n520: \n521: # Interface compliance check\n522: go build ./...\n523: \n524: # Lint check\n525: make lint PKG=./pkg/store/...\n526: ```\n527: \n528: ### Test Scenarios\n529: \n530: | Scenario | Expected Result |\n531: |----------|-----------------|\n532: | Store and retrieve sandbox | Success, data matches |\n533: | Get non-existent session | ErrNotFound returned |\n534: | Update existing session | Success, data updated |\n535: | Update non-existent session | Error \"key not exists\" |\n536: | Delete session | Not found on subsequent get |\n537: | List expired sessions | Returns only expired entries |\n538: | List with limit=0 | Returns nil, nil |\n539: | Update activity for missing session | ErrNotFound returned |\n540: | Orphan ZSET member | Skipped during list, no error |\n541: | Concurrent stores | All succeed (different session IDs) |\n542: | STORE_TYPE=valkey selection | Valkey implementation initialized |\n543: | STORE_TYPE unset (default) | Redis implementation initialized |\n544: \n545: ---\n546: \n547: ## References\n548: \n549: - [Session Store Design](session-store/design.md) — Detailed design document\n550: - [Session Store Specification](session-store/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n551: - [AR-013 Proposal](proposal.md) — Redis implementation (this file replaced)\n552: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n553: - [Valkey Go Client](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go) — Valkey client reference\n554: - [Valkey Documentation](https://valkey.io/) — Valkey server reference\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ## Success Criteria\n559: \n560: 1. ✅ All 8 Store interface methods implemented for Valkey\n561: 2. ✅ `DoMulti`-based atomic operations for Store and Delete\n562: 3. ✅ `ErrNotFound` returned for missing keys (via `IsValkeyNil`)\n563: 4. ✅ ZSET indexes correctly maintained\n564: 5. ✅ Environment-based configuration works (VALKEY_* variables)\n565: 6. ✅ `STORE_TYPE=valkey` correctly selects Valkey provider\n566: 7. ✅ All integration tests pass against Valkey instance\n567: 8. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n568: 9. ✅ `Storage()` singleton properly initializes via `sync.Once`\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: *AR-014 — Module: pkg/store — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 572 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Valkey Storage Implementation\n\n## AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/store` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | S (Small) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a Valkey storage provider as an alternative to the existing Redis backend for the Session Store interface. This proposal delivers a production-ready Valkey implementation that:\n\n1. **Implements the Store Interface**: Full implementation of all 8 Store methods using `valkey-go` client\n2. **Provides Atomic Operations**: `DoMulti`-based multi-command transactions for data consistency\n3. **Maintains Secondary Indexes**: ZSET-based expiry and activity tracking for efficient garbage collection","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871169511,"end":1775871169536}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871169545,"sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2b86320013DtaXoR7mIBhaY","messageID":"msg_d7a2b7571001vfOFNt4osdhxpl","sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n14: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n15: │  CommandExecutor  │  ExecutionManager  │  OutputBuffer  │\n16: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n17: │              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n18: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n19: │              Resource Limiter (Integration)              │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Key Interfaces\n24: \n25: #### CommandExecutor\n26: \n27: The primary interface for executing commands through PicoD.\n28: \n29: ```go\n30: type CommandExecutor interface {\n31:     Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n32:     ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n33:     GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n34:     Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n35:     StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n36: }\n37: ```\n38: \n39: #### ExecutionRequest\n40: \n41: Configuration for a command execution.\n42: \n43: ```go\n44: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n45:     Command     string\n46:     Args        []string\n47:     WorkingDir  string\n48:     Environment map[string]string\n49:     Timeout     time.Duration\n50:     ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n51:     SessionID   string\n52: }\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### ExecutionResult\n56: \n57: Result of a command execution.\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: type ExecutionResult struct {\n61:     ID         ExecutionID\n62:     Status     ExecutionStatus\n63:     ExitCode   int\n64:     Stdout     []byte\n65:     Stderr     []byte\n66:     StartedAt  time.Time\n67:     FinishedAt time.Time\n68:     Error      *ExecutionError\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ## Data Flow\n73: \n74: ### Synchronous Execution\n75: \n76: ```\n77: 1. Client calls Execute()\n78: 2. PicoD validates request and resource limits\n79: 3. Sandbox environment is prepared\n80: 4. Command is executed with monitoring\n81: 5. Output is captured\n82: 6. Result is returned to client\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ### Asynchronous Execution\n86: \n87: ```\n88: 1. Client calls ExecuteAsync()\n89: 2. Execution is queued with initial status \"pending\"\n90: 3. Background worker picks up execution\n91: 4. Status updates to \"running\"\n92: 5. Output is streamed to buffer\n93: 6. On completion, status updates to \"completed\" or \"failed\"\n94: 7. Client polls GetStatus() or receives callback\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ## Error Handling\n98: \n99: ### Error Types\n100: \n101: - `ErrInvalidRequest`: Malformed execution request\n102: - `ErrResourceExceeded`: Resource limits exceeded\n103: - `ErrTimeout`: Execution exceeded timeout\n104: - `ErrSandboxUnavailable`: Sandbox environment not available\n105: - `ErrExecutionFailed`: Command returned non-zero exit code\n106: - `ErrCancelled`: Execution was cancelled\n107: \n108: ### Status States\n109: \n110: ```\n111: pending → running → completed\n112:               ↓\n113:             failed\n114:               ↓\n115:            cancelled\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ## Security Considerations\n119: \n120: - Commands run in isolated sandbox environment\n121: - Resource limits enforced at sandbox level\n122: - No direct shell access\n123: - Environment variable filtering\n124: - Working directory restrictions\n125: \n126: ## Performance Considerations\n127: \n128: - Connection pooling to sandbox service\n129: - Output buffering with size limits\n130: - Concurrent execution limits\n131: - Timeout enforcement at multiple levels\n132: \n133: ## Open Questions\n134: \n135: 1. Maximum output size limits?\n136: 2. Real-time streaming protocol?\n137: 3. Multi-tenancy isolation model?\n138: 4. Execution queue prioritization?\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  CommandExecutor  │  ExecutionManager  │  OutputBuffer  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Resource Limiter (Integration)              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","time":{"start":1775871169514,"end":1775871169543}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871169547,"sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2b8ad00010mLh0DxPF0WmUc","messageID":"msg_d7a2b7571001vfOFNt4osdhxpl","sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Changes to Existing Code\n4: \n5: ### New Files\n6: \n7: ```\n8: pkg/picod/\n9: ├── executor.go       # Core CommandExecutor implementation\n10: ├── executor_test.go  # Unit tests\n11: ├── types.go          # Request/response types\n12: ├── status.go         # Execution status management\n13: ├── output.go         # Output capture and streaming\n14: └── errors.go         # Error definitions\n15: ```\n16: \n17: ### Interfaces Added\n18: \n19: ```go\n20: // pkg/picod/types.go\n21: \n22: type ExecutionID string\n23: \n24: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n25:     Command        string\n26:     Args           []string\n27:     WorkingDir     string\n28:     Environment    map[string]string\n29:     Timeout        time.Duration\n30:     ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n31:     SessionID      string\n32: }\n33: \n34: type ExecutionResult struct {\n35:     ID         ExecutionID\n36:     Status     ExecutionStatus\n37:     ExitCode   int\n38:     Stdout     []byte\n39:     Stderr     []byte\n40:     StartedAt  time.Time\n41:     FinishedAt time.Time\n42:     Error      *ExecutionError\n43: }\n44: \n45: type ExecutionStatus struct {\n46:     ID         ExecutionID\n47:     State      ExecutionState\n48:     StartedAt  *time.Time\n49:     FinishedAt *time.Time\n50:     ExitCode   *int\n51: }\n52: \n53: type ExecutionState string\n54: \n55: const (\n56:     StatePending    ExecutionState = \"pending\"\n57:     StateRunning    ExecutionState = \"running\"\n58:     StateCompleted  ExecutionState = \"completed\"\n59:     StateFailed     ExecutionState = \"failed\"\n60:     StateCancelled  ExecutionState = \"cancelled\"\n61: )\n62: \n63: type ResourceConstraints struct {\n64:     MaxMemory   int64         // bytes\n65:     MaxCPU      float64       // percentage\n66:     MaxIOBytes  int64         // bytes per second\n67:     MaxFiles    int\n68: }\n69: \n70: type ExecutionError struct {\n71:     Code    string\n72:     Message string\n73:     Details map[string]interface{}\n74: }\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ### Dependencies\n78: \n79: - `pkg/sandbox` (AR-009): Sandbox interface for command execution\n80: - `pkg/store` (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014): For execution status persistence\n81: \n82: ### Configuration\n83: \n84: New configuration options:\n85: \n86: ```yaml\n87: picod:\n88:   default_timeout: 30s\n89:   max_concurrent_executions: 100\n90:   max_output_size: 10MB\n91:   output_buffer_size: 4KB\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ## API Surface\n95: \n96: ### Public API\n97: \n98: ```go\n99: // NewCommandExecutor creates a new PicoD command executor\n100: func NewCommandExecutor(sandbox SandboxClient, store StatusStore, opts ExecutorOptions) (*CommandExecutor, error)\n101: \n102: // Execute runs a command synchronously\n103: func (e *CommandExecutor) Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n104: \n105: // ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously\n106: func (e *CommandExecutor) ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n107: \n108: // GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution\n109: func (e *CommandExecutor) GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n110: \n111: // Cancel stops a running execution\n112: func (e *CommandExecutor) Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n113: \n114: // StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output\n115: func (e *CommandExecutor) StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ## Behavioral Changes\n119: \n120: - Commands are now executed through PicoD API instead of direct sandbox calls\n121: - Resource limits are enforced at the API layer\n122: - All executions are tracked with persistent status\n123: - Output is captured and can be streamed\n124: \n125: ## Migration Notes\n126: \n127: - Existing direct sandbox usage should migrate to PicoD API\n128: - No breaking changes to sandbox interface\n129: - PicoD API is additive layer on top of existing components\n\n(End of file - total 129 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Delta Specification\n\n## Changes to Existing Code\n\n### New Files\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── executor.go       # Core CommandExecutor implementation\n├── executor_test.go  # Unit tests\n├── types.go          # Request/response types\n├── status.go         # Execution status management\n├── output.go         # Output capture and streaming\n└── errors.go         # Error definitions\n```\n\n### Interfaces Added\n\n```go\n// pkg/picod/types.go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871169516,"end":1775871169546}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871169550,"sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2b8f810012BTn7HmuEsTHHN","messageID":"msg_d7a2b7571001vfOFNt4osdhxpl","sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD command execution API.\n6: \n7: ## Phase 1: API Design and Interface Definition\n8: \n9: - [ ] Define command execution request/response structures\n10: - [ ] Design PicoD client interface\n11: - [ ] Define execution options (timeout, resource limits, env vars)\n12: - [ ] Document error codes and status states\n13: \n14: ## Phase 2: Core Implementation\n15: \n16: - [ ] Implement CommandExecutor struct and methods\n17: - [ ] Implement synchronous execution flow\n18: - [ ] Implement asynchronous execution with status tracking\n19: - [ ] Add resource limit integration points\n20: \n21: ## Phase 3: Output Handling\n22: \n23: - [ ] Design output capture mechanism\n24: - [ ] Implement stdout/stderr collection\n25: - [ ] Add output streaming support (buffer-based)\n26: - [ ] Handle large output scenarios\n27: \n28: ## Phase 4: Error Handling and Status\n29: \n30: - [ ] Implement execution status lifecycle\n31: - [ ] Add timeout and cancellation support\n32: - [ ] Design error translation layer\n33: - [ ] Add execution result metadata\n34: \n35: ## Phase 5: Testing\n36: \n37: - [ ] Write unit tests for execution logic\n38: - [ ] Create mock sandbox for testing\n39: - [ ] Add integration tests\n40: - [ ] Performance and resource limit tests\n41: \n42: ## Dependencies\n43: \n44: - AR-009: Sandbox orchestration system (for integration)\n45: - AR-012: Session storage interface (for status persistence)\n46: \n47: ## Estimated Timeline\n48: \n49: - Phase 1: 1 day\n50: - Phase 2: 1.5 days\n51: - Phase 3: 1 day\n52: - Phase 4: 0.5 day\n53: - Phase 5: 1 day\n54: \n55: Total: 4-5 days\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Implementation Plan\n\n## Overview\n\nThis plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD command execution API.\n\n## Phase 1: API Design and Interface Definition\n\n- [ ] Define command execution request/response structures\n- [ ] Design PicoD client interface\n- [ ] Define execution options (timeout, resource limits, env vars)\n- [ ] Document error codes and status states\n\n## Phase 2: Core Implementation\n\n- [ ] Implement CommandExecutor struct and methods\n- [ ] Implement synchronous execution flow\n- [ ] Implement asynchronous execution with status tracking\n- [ ] Add resource limit integration points\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md","time":{"start":1775871169519,"end":1775871169548}}}}
