{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871282346,"sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2bfc3b001LBTygwhsfRzfNC","messageID":"msg_d7a2bd478001yrSOvtHQcoe7JW","sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/picod` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the PicoD command execution API that provides a unified interface for executing commands within sandboxed environments. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **Synchronous and Asynchronous Execution**: Support for both immediate command execution and long-running background tasks with status tracking\n2. **Resource Management**: Integration with resource constraints to enforce limits on memory, CPU, and I/O\n3. **Output Capture and Streaming**: Buffer-based output collection with real-time streaming capabilities\n4. **Execution Lifecycle Management**: Complete state machine for command execution from pending through completion or cancellation\n\nThis API serves as the primary interface between the agentcube platform and the sandbox orchestration system, enabling secure, monitored command execution with full observability.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **CommandExecutor Interface** | Core execution interface with sync/async methods |\n| **Execution Types** | `ExecutionRequest`, `ExecutionResult`, `ExecutionStatus` |\n| **State Management** | Execution state lifecycle (pending → running → completed/failed/cancelled) |\n| **Synchronous Execution** | Blocking command execution with timeout support |\n| **Asynchronous Execution** | Non-blocking execution with status polling |\n| **Output Handling** | Stdout/stderr capture and streaming via channels |\n| **Cancellation** | Graceful and forceful execution cancellation |\n| **Resource Constraints** | Memory, CPU, I/O, and file descriptor limits |\n| **Error Types** | Domain-specific errors for execution failures |\n| **Status Store Integration** | Persistence layer for execution state tracking |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Changes to the sandbox orchestration interface (AR-009)\n- Modifications to storage implementations (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)\n- HTTP server implementation (separate PicoD daemon)\n- JWT authentication layer\n- File upload/download APIs\n- Interactive command support (stdin streaming)\n- Command chaining and pipe operations\n- Multi-tenancy isolation beyond sandbox level\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File Structure\n\n| File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n|------|------|--------------|\n| `pkg/picod/executor.go` | CommandExecutor implementation | ~250 |\n| `pkg/picod/types.go` | Request/response type definitions | ~100 |\n| `pkg/picod/status.go` | Execution status management | ~80 |\n| `pkg/picod/output.go` | Output capture and streaming | ~120 |\n| `pkg/picod/errors.go` | Error type definitions | ~50 |\n| `pkg/picod/executor_test.go` | Unit tests | ~200 |\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Client Application                    │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              PicoD CommandExecutor API                   │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Execute()  │  ExecuteAsync()  │  GetStatus()          │\n│  Cancel()   │  StreamOutput()  │                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Status Store (AR-012/13/14)                 │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Core Types\n\n#### ExecutionRequest\n\n```go\ntype ExecutionRequest struct {\n    Command        string\n    Args           []string\n    WorkingDir     string\n    Environment    map[string]string\n    Timeout        time.Duration\n    ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n    SessionID      string\n}\n```\n\n#### ExecutionResult\n\n```go\ntype ExecutionResult struct {\n    ID         ExecutionID\n    Status     ExecutionStatus\n    ExitCode   int\n    Stdout     []byte\n    Stderr     []byte\n    StartedAt  time.Time\n    FinishedAt time.Time\n    Error      *ExecutionError\n}\n```\n\n#### ExecutionStatus\n\n```go\ntype ExecutionStatus struct {\n    ID         ExecutionID\n    State      ExecutionState\n    StartedAt  *time.Time\n    FinishedAt *time.Time\n    ExitCode   *int\n}\n\n type ExecutionState string\n\nconst (\n    StatePending    ExecutionState = \"pending\"\n    StateRunning    ExecutionState = \"running\"\n    StateCompleted  ExecutionState = \"completed\"\n    StateFailed     ExecutionState = \"failed\"\n    StateCancelled  ExecutionState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\n#### ResourceConstraints\n\n```go\ntype ResourceConstraints struct {\n    MaxMemory   int64         // bytes\n    MaxCPU      float64       // percentage\n    MaxIOBytes  int64         // bytes per second\n    MaxFiles    int\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Execution Flows\n\n### Synchronous Execution\n\n```\nExecute(ctx, req)\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate request parameters\n    │\n    ▼\nGenerate ExecutionID\n    │\n    ▼\nCheck resource availability\n    │\n    ▼\nPrepare sandbox environment\n    │\n    ▼\nExecute command with timeout context\n    │\n    ▼\nCapture stdout/stderr\n    │\n    ▼\nBuild ExecutionResult\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn result\n```\n\n### Asynchronous Execution\n\n```\nExecuteAsync(ctx, req)\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate request parameters\n    │\n    ▼\nGenerate ExecutionID\n    │\n    ▼\nCreate initial status (StatePending)\n    │\n    ▼\nQueue execution for background worker\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn ExecutionID immediately\n\nBackground Worker:\n    │\n    ▼\nPick pending execution\n    │\n    ▼\nUpdate status to StateRunning\n    │\n    ▼\nExecute command\n    │\n    ▼\nStream output to buffer\n    │\n    ▼\nOn completion:\n    ├─ Success → StateCompleted\n    ├─ Failure → StateFailed\n    └─ Cancelled → StateCancelled\n```\n\n### Status Retrieval\n\n```\nGetStatus(ctx, id)\n    │\n    ▼\nQuery status store for execution record\n    │\n    ▼\nIf not found:\n    └── Return ErrExecutionNotFound\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn ExecutionStatus\n```\n\n### Cancellation Flow\n\n```\nCancel(ctx, id)\n    │\n    ▼\nRetrieve current status\n    │\n    ▼\nIf not found:\n    └── Return ErrExecutionNotFound\n    │\n    ▼\nIf StateCompleted/StateFailed/StateCancelled:\n    └── Return ErrAlreadyFinished\n    │\n    ▼\nSend cancellation signal\n    │\n    ▼\nUpdate status to StateCancelled\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn nil\n```\n\n### Output Streaming\n\n```\nStreamOutput(ctx, id)\n    │\n    ▼\nCreate output channel\n    │\n    ▼\nStart streaming goroutine\n    │\n    ▼\nFor each output chunk:\n    ├─ Read from buffer\n    ├─ Send to channel\n    └─ Check for ctx cancellation\n    │\n    ▼\nClose channel on completion\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn channel to caller\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n| Error | Code | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `ErrInvalidRequest` | `INVALID_REQUEST` | Malformed execution request |\n| `ErrResourceExceeded` | `RESOURCE_EXCEEDED` | Resource limits exceeded |\n| `ErrTimeout` | `TIMEOUT` | Execution exceeded timeout |\n| `ErrSandboxUnavailable` | `SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE` | Sandbox environment not available |\n| `ErrExecutionFailed` | `EXECUTION_FAILED` | Command returned non-zero exit code |\n| `ErrCancelled` | `CANCELLED` | Execution was cancelled |\n| `ErrExecutionNotFound` | `NOT_FOUND` | Execution ID does not exist |\n| `ErrAlreadyFinished` | `ALREADY_FINISHED` | Cannot cancel completed execution |\n\n### ExecutionError Structure\n\n```go\ntype ExecutionError struct {\n    Code    string\n    Message string\n    Details map[string]interface{}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files Created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n|------|--------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/picod/executor.go` | ~250 | Core executor implementation |\n| `pkg/picod/types.go` | ~100 | Type definitions |\n| `pkg/picod/status.go` | ~80 | Status management |\n| `pkg/picod/output.go` | ~120 | Output capture and streaming |\n| `pkg/picod/errors.go` | ~50 | Error definitions |\n| `pkg/picod/executor_test.go` | ~200 | Unit tests |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"sync\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/sandbox\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n)\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `pkg/sandbox` | Sandbox interface for command execution (AR-009) |\n| `pkg/store` | Status persistence interface (AR-012/13/14) |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Session Manager | Execute user commands within sessions |\n| Idle Cleanup Worker | Query active executions before cleanup |\n| HTTP API Layer | REST endpoints for command execution |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|-------|\n| Execute (sync) | O(1) | Blocking until completion |\n| ExecuteAsync | O(1) | Queue insertion |\n| GetStatus | O(1) | Store lookup |\n| Cancel | O(1) | Signal + status update |\n| StreamOutput | O(n) | n = output chunks |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Direct Sandbox Integration Without API Layer\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Simpler architecture; fewer abstraction layers |\n| **Cons** | No centralized execution tracking; resource limits scattered; harder to implement async execution |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — API layer provides necessary abstraction for status tracking, resource management, and async operations |\n\n### Alternative 2: gRPC Instead of In-Process API\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Cross-language support; network transparency |\n| **Cons** | Additional complexity; serialization overhead; not needed for in-cluster communication |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — In-process Go interface is simpler and sufficient for current requirements |\n\n### Alternative 3: Event-Driven Execution Model\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Better decoupling; natural fit for async operations |\n| **Cons** | Higher complexity; harder to implement synchronous operations |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Direct method calls provide better control and simpler error handling |\n\n### Alternative 4: Integration with Existing Workflow Engines\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Mature solutions (Temporal, Cadence); built-in persistence |\n| **Cons** | Heavy dependencies; overkill for command execution needs; operational complexity |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Custom lightweight implementation better fits the specific use case |\n\n---\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Resource leaks on cancellation | Low | High | Ensure proper cleanup in defer blocks; use context cancellation |\n| Memory exhaustion from large output | Low | High | Implement output size limits; streaming for large outputs |\n| Status store inconsistency | Low | Medium | Atomic updates; reconciliation loop for orphaned entries |\n| Concurrent execution limits | Medium | Medium | Configurable concurrency limits; proper queue management |\n| Sandbox integration failures | Medium | High | Graceful error handling; fallback to error status |\n| Goroutine leaks in streaming | Low | Medium | Proper channel closure; context cancellation handling |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all picod tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/picod/...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/picod/...\n\n# Run specific test categories\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestExecute\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestAsync\"\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run integration tests (requires sandbox)\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/... -tags=integration\n\n# With coverage\ngo test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out\n```\n\n### Manual Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/picod/...\n\n# Interface compliance check\ngo build ./...\n\n# Lint check\nmake lint PKG=./pkg/picod/...\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----------|-----------------|\n| Sync execution success | Returns ExecutionResult with exit code 0 |\n| Sync execution timeout | Returns ErrTimeout, exit code 124 |\n| Sync execution failure | Returns ExecutionResult with non-zero exit code |\n| Async execution | Returns ExecutionID immediately |\n| Status polling | Returns correct state transitions |\n| Cancellation | Execution stops, status becomes cancelled |\n| Output streaming | All output chunks received in order |\n| Resource limit exceeded | Returns ErrResourceExceeded |\n| Invalid command | Returns ErrExecutionFailed |\n| Concurrent executions | All execute independently |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [PicoD Design](changes/AR-015/design.md) — Detailed design document\n- [PicoD Delta Spec](changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md) — API specification changes\n- [PicoD Tests](changes/AR-015/tests.md) — Test specifications\n- [Code Execution Spec](code-execution/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n- [AR-009 Sandbox](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) — Sandbox orchestration system\n- [AR-012 Session Store](session-store/design.md) — Storage interface\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ CommandExecutor interface fully implemented\n2. ✅ Synchronous execution with timeout support\n3. ✅ Asynchronous execution with status tracking\n4. ✅ Output capture and streaming functionality\n5. ✅ Cancellation support for running executions\n6. ✅ Resource constraint validation and enforcement\n7. ✅ Complete state lifecycle management\n8. ✅ Unit test coverage >= 85%\n9. ✅ Integration tests passing\n10. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n\n---\n\n*AR-015 — Module: pkg/picod — Language: Go — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871282258,"end":1775871282343}}}}
