{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871286324,"sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2d579e001G147NtPTWsaKmT","messageID":"msg_d7a2d4ce6001kVGUStaO66KgE2","sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `pkg/picod` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the PicoD command execution API that provides a unified interface for executing commands within sandboxed environments. This proposal delivers:\n17: \n18: 1. **Synchronous and Asynchronous Execution**: Support for both immediate command execution and long-running background tasks with status tracking\n19: 2. **Resource Management**: Integration with resource constraints to enforce limits on memory, CPU, and I/O\n20: 3. **Output Capture and Streaming**: Buffer-based output collection with real-time streaming capabilities\n21: 4. **Execution Lifecycle Management**: Complete state machine for command execution from pending through completion or cancellation\n22: \n23: This API serves as the primary interface between the agentcube platform and the sandbox orchestration system, enabling secure, monitored command execution with full observability.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Scope\n28: \n29: ### In Scope\n30: \n31: | Item | Detail |\n32: |------|--------|\n33: | **CommandExecutor Interface** | Core execution interface with sync/async methods |\n34: | **Execution Types** | `ExecutionRequest`, `ExecutionResult`, `ExecutionStatus` |\n35: | **State Management** | Execution state lifecycle (pending → running → completed/failed/cancelled) |\n36: | **Synchronous Execution** | Blocking command execution with timeout support |\n37: | **Asynchronous Execution** | Non-blocking execution with status polling |\n38: | **Output Handling** | Stdout/stderr capture and streaming via channels |\n39: | **Cancellation** | Graceful and forceful execution cancellation |\n40: | **Resource Constraints** | Memory, CPU, I/O, and file descriptor limits |\n41: | **Error Types** | Domain-specific errors for execution failures |\n42: | **Status Store Integration** | Persistence layer for execution state tracking |\n43: \n44: ### Out of Scope\n45: \n46: - Changes to the sandbox orchestration interface (AR-009)\n47: - Modifications to storage implementations (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)\n48: - HTTP server implementation (separate PicoD daemon)\n49: - JWT authentication layer\n50: - File upload/download APIs\n51: - Interactive command support (stdin streaming)\n52: - Command chaining and pipe operations\n53: - Multi-tenancy isolation beyond sandbox level\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Design\n58: \n59: ### File Structure\n60: \n61: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n62: |------|------|--------------|\n63: | `pkg/picod/executor.go` | CommandExecutor implementation | ~250 |\n64: | `pkg/picod/types.go` | Request/response type definitions | ~100 |\n65: | `pkg/picod/status.go` | Execution status management | ~80 |\n66: | `pkg/picod/output.go` | Output capture and streaming | ~120 |\n67: | `pkg/picod/errors.go` | Error type definitions | ~50 |\n68: | `pkg/picod/executor_test.go` | Unit tests | ~200 |\n69: \n70: ### Architecture\n71: \n72: ```\n73: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n74: │                    Client Application                    │\n75: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘\n76:                       │\n77:                       ▼\n78: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n79: │              PicoD CommandExecutor API                   │\n80: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n81: │  Execute()  │  ExecuteAsync()  │  GetStatus()          │\n82: │  Cancel()   │  StreamOutput()  │                       │\n83: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n84: │              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n85: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n86: │              Status Store (AR-012/13/14)                 │\n87: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Core Types\n91: \n92: #### ExecutionRequest\n93: \n94: ```go\n95: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n96:     Command        string\n97:     Args           []string\n98:     WorkingDir     string\n99:     Environment    map[string]string\n100:     Timeout        time.Duration\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 510. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/picod` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the PicoD command execution API that provides a unified interface for executing commands within sandboxed environments. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **Synchronous and Asynchronous Execution**: Support for both immediate command execution and long-running background tasks with status tracking\n2. **Resource Management**: Integration with resource constraints to enforce limits on memory, CPU, and I/O\n3. **Output Capture and Streaming**: Buffer-based output collection with real-time streaming capabilities","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871286311,"end":1775871286321}}}}
