{"type":"text","timestamp":1775871298464,"sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2d6b08001yE6D1fz2LBflA3","messageID":"msg_d7a2d5c69001SrbvNA9593DZ8H","sessionID":"ses_285d4defaffe6DUSOvUo0HSAee","type":"text","text":"The proposal.md has been successfully written. Here's a summary of the document:\n\n## Proposal: AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API\n\nThe proposal includes:\n\n### 📋 Header\n- **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M (Medium)\n- **Status**: Proposed\n\n### 📑 Sections Included\n1. **Purpose** — Describes the PicoD command execution API providing sync/async execution, resource management, output capture, and lifecycle management\n\n2. **Scope** — In-scope items (CommandExecutor interface, execution types, state management, sync/async execution, output handling, cancellation, resource constraints) and out-of-scope items\n\n3. **Design** — File structure (~800 lines total), architecture diagram, and core type definitions (ExecutionRequest, ExecutionResult, ExecutionStatus, ResourceConstraints)\n\n4. **Execution Flows** — ASCII diagrams showing synchronous execution, asynchronous execution, status retrieval, cancellation, and output streaming flows\n\n5. **Error Handling** — Error types table and ExecutionError structure\n\n6. **Impact Analysis** — Files created (~800 lines), dependencies (pkg/sandbox, pkg/store), downstream consumers, and performance characteristics\n\n7. **Alternatives Considered** — Four alternatives evaluated:\n   - Direct sandbox integration (rejected)\n   - gRPC instead of in-process API (rejected)\n   - Event-driven execution model (rejected)\n   - Integration with existing workflow engines (rejected)\n\n8. **Risks and Mitigations** — Six identified risks with likelihood, impact, and mitigation strategies\n\n9. **Verification** — Unit tests, integration tests, manual verification commands, and test scenarios table\n\n10. **References** — Links to design.md, delta-spec.md, tests.md, and related ARs\n\n11. **Success Criteria** — 10 checkboxes for completion criteria","time":{"start":1775871298462,"end":1775871298462}}}
